## Auth invalid

> Example `auth.invalid` Event

```json
{
  "_id": "580e3e11dec21e861b5a3719",
  "type": "auth.invalid",
  "created": "2016-04-20T16:51:12Z",
  "payload": {
    "resource": {
      "type": "auth",
      "id": "579b695decfa11012711875d"
    },
    "data": { 
      "company" : {
        "_id" : "55942f330cfcfd6c4ed529d8",
        "name" : "Geico"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

When the credentials no longer work with the company's website and need to be reauthenticated.

Attribute | Description
--------- | -----------
`type` | `auth.invalid`
`payload.data.company` | The [company object](#the-company-object) linked to this resource.